    <item>
      <title>Delta</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/delta/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/delta/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Delta (&lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;Δ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\Delta&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) is the semiotic difference operation in the &lt;a href=&#34;../interactive-semioverse.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Interactive Semioverse&lt;/a&gt;, defined at three levels. &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Signs&lt;/a&gt; become distinguishable through relational encounter — what one handle engages that another does not. Delta formalizes this relational differentiation at increasing depth. At the interaction level, &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;Δ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;i&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∖&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∪&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;B&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∖&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;A&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\Delta_{\mathrm{ix}}(A, B) = (A \setminus B) \cup (B \setminus A)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the symmetric difference of two &lt;a href=&#34;./interaction-surface.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interaction surfaces&lt;/a&gt;. At the &lt;a href=&#34;../../semiotic-universe/terms/fragment.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;fragment&lt;/a&gt; level, &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;Δ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;r&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\Delta_{\mathrm{frag}}(F, G)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the least fragment containing &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∪&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∖&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∩&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;G&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;(F \cup G) \setminus (F \cap G)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. At the &lt;a href=&#34;./footprint.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;footprint&lt;/a&gt; level, &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;Δ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;;&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;script&#34;&gt;S&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;Δ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;r&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;g&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\Delta_{\mathrm{foot}}(\tau, \tau&amp;#x27;; X) = \mathcal{S}_X(\Delta_{\mathrm{frag}}(F_{\tau,X}, F_{\tau&amp;#x27;,X}))&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — the closure of the fragment delta.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Footprint</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/footprint/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/footprint/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;semiotic&lt;/a&gt; footprint of a &lt;a href=&#34;./handle.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handle&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\tau&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in state &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;X&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the closed partial state obtained by applying the composite &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../concepts/closure-operator/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;closure operator&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;script&#34;&gt;S&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathcal{S}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; to the &lt;a href=&#34;./handle-fragment.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handle fragment&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;o&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;script&#34;&gt;S&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathrm{Foot}_X(\tau) = \mathcal{S}_X(F_{\tau,X})&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. The footprint formalizes &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../general/people/charles-sanders-peirce.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Peirce&amp;rsquo;s&lt;/a&gt; pragmatic maxim: the meaning of a &lt;a href=&#34;./handle.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handle&lt;/a&gt; is the totality of its conceivable practical effects — the full semantic, syntactic, and &lt;a href=&#34;../../semiotic-universe/terms/fusion.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;fusion&lt;/a&gt; closure of everything generated by the handle&amp;rsquo;s interactions.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The footprint is always bounded by the core semioverse state X*: for any X &amp;lt;= X* and any tau, Foot_X(tau) &amp;lt;= X*. This boundedness ensures that no single handle&amp;rsquo;s interactions can produce semantic material beyond what the semioverse&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../concepts/fixed-point/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;least fixed point&lt;/a&gt; contains. The footprint is also monotone in the &lt;a href=&#34;./interaction-surface.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interaction surface&lt;/a&gt;: more interactions produce a larger or equal footprint.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Handle</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/handle/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/handle/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A handle is a persistent &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/index-sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;indexical&lt;/a&gt; reference that points to a thing in the &lt;a href=&#34;../interactive-semioverse.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Interactive Semioverse&lt;/a&gt;. In Peirce&amp;rsquo;s trichotomy, an &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/index-sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;index&lt;/a&gt; is a &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;sign&lt;/a&gt; connected to its object by existential relation rather than convention or resemblance. A handle formalizes this: it is not an &lt;a href=&#34;../../../sets/terms/element.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;element&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../concepts/heyting-algebra/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Heyting algebra&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — it lives outside the semantic domain and participates only through &lt;a href=&#34;./interaction-term.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interaction terms&lt;/a&gt;. The set of all handles is denoted &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;l&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;e&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathsf{Handle}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Each handle has a semantic seed &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;η&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\eta(\tau)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, which is the only point where the handle touches semantics directly. Everything else — the handle&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href=&#34;./interaction-surface.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interaction surface&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;./handle-fragment.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handle fragment&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&#34;./footprint.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;footprint&lt;/a&gt; — is mediated through &lt;a href=&#34;./interaction-term.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interaction terms&lt;/a&gt; and closure. This indirection captures the semiotic principle that an &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/index-sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;index&lt;/a&gt; is never fully described by the meaning it currently conveys — it maintains an existential connection that may generate further meaning through further interaction.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Handle Fragment</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/handle-fragment/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/handle-fragment/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The handle fragment &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F_{\tau,X}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; of a handle &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\tau&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in state &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;X&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the least &lt;a href=&#34;../../semiotic-universe/terms/fragment.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;fragment&lt;/a&gt; containing the semantic interpretations of &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\tau&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href=&#34;./interaction-surface.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interaction surface&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;F&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;F_{\tau,X}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; = the least fragment containing &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;{&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;⟦&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;⟧&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∈&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;I&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;}&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\{\llbracket t\rrbracket : t \in \mathrm{Ix}_X(\tau)\}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. It is the smallest modal–trace &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../general/people/arend-heyting.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Heyting&lt;/a&gt; subalgebra of &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; generated by the handle&amp;rsquo;s interaction denotations — the bounded interpretive context generated by a handle&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;semiotic&lt;/a&gt; encounters.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The handle fragment captures everything that can be inferred locally from the handle&amp;rsquo;s interactions, before applying the full &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../concepts/closure-operator/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;closure operator&lt;/a&gt;. It is monotone in the &lt;a href=&#34;./interaction-surface.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interaction surface&lt;/a&gt;: adding &lt;a href=&#34;./interaction-term.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interaction terms&lt;/a&gt; can only enlarge the handle fragment. The handle fragment sits inside H and is subject to all the fragment-level reasoning tools &amp;ndash; fragmentwise equality, hereditary extensionality, and the &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../disciplines/higher-topos-theory/terms/sheaf-condition.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;sheaf condition&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Interaction Surface</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/interaction-surface/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/interaction-surface/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The interaction surface of a &lt;a href=&#34;./handle.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handle&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\tau&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in a partial state &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;X&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is the finite set of &lt;a href=&#34;./interaction-term.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interaction terms&lt;/a&gt; associated with &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\tau&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in that state: &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;I&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⊆&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;I&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;e&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;r&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;m&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathrm{Ix}_X(\tau) \subseteq \mathsf{IxTerm}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. The interaction surface is the boundary across which the handle engages with the meaning domain — it records which semiotic acts are currently active for the handle. It is the relational boundary across which external engagement is translated into the sign system&amp;rsquo;s internal meaning.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;An interaction surface is not itself semantic content; it is auxiliary data that mediates between &lt;a href=&#34;./handle.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handles&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../concepts/heyting-algebra/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Heyting algebra&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. Semantic consequences are produced by interpreting the terms and generating the &lt;a href=&#34;./handle-fragment.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handle fragment&lt;/a&gt; from their denotations. Enlarging the interaction surface (adding more &lt;a href=&#34;./interaction-term.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;interaction terms&lt;/a&gt;) can only enlarge the handle fragment: if &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;I&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⊆&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msubsup&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;I&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;X&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msubsup&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathrm{Ix}_X(\tau) \subseteq \mathrm{Ix}&amp;#x27;_X(\tau)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, then the handle fragment under the larger surface contains the one under the smaller.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Interaction Term</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/interaction-term/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/interaction-term/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;An interaction term is a structured semiotic act — an expression built from &lt;a href=&#34;./handle.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handles&lt;/a&gt; (the things pointed at) and definable operators (the ways of combining what is pointed at), interpreted into the &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../concepts/heyting-algebra/index.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Heyting algebra&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. Interaction terms form the smallest set &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;I&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;x&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;T&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;e&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;r&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;m&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathsf{IxTerm}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; generated by: &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;:&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∣&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;k&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;…&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;t ::= \tau \mid k(t_1, \dots, t_n)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, where &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\tau&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is a &lt;a href=&#34;./handle.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;k&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;k&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is a definable operator in &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;O&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;sans-serif&#34;&gt;p&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;d&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;e&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;f&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\mathsf{Op}^{\mathrm{def}}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Interpretation extends recursively: a &lt;a href=&#34;./handle.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handle&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\tau&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; interprets as its semantic seed &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;η&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;τ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\eta(\tau)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, and an operator application &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;k&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;…&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;k(t_1, \dots, t_n)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; interprets as &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;⟦&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;k&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;⟧&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;⟦&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;⟧&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo&gt;…&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo separator=&#34;true&#34;&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;⟦&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;msub&gt;&lt;mi&gt;t&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/msub&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34; lspace=&#34;0em&#34; rspace=&#34;0em&#34;&gt;⟧&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;\llbracket k\rrbracket(\llbracket t_1\rrbracket, \dots, \llbracket t_n\rrbracket)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. Interaction terms are the semiotic acts through which &lt;a href=&#34;./handle.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;handles&lt;/a&gt; produce semantic material in &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;H&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;H&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — the only way external entities generate content in the &lt;a href=&#34;../interactive-semioverse.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Interactive Semioverse&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Subtraction</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/subtraction/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 31 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/terms/subtraction/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Subtraction in the &lt;a href=&#34;../interactive-semioverse.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Interactive Semioverse&lt;/a&gt; is a disciplined operation for semiotic forgetting, built from the &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../disciplines/logic/terms/heyting-implication.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Heyting implication&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Sign&lt;/a&gt; systems do not only grow — they also forget. The Heyting pseudocomplement provides the right notion of removal in an intuitionistic setting: at the element level, &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⊖&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;=&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∧&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;⇒&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;⊥&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=&#34;false&#34;&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;a \ominus b = a \wedge (b \Rightarrow \bot)&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; — the &lt;a href=&#34;../../../posets/terms/meet.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;meet&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;a&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; with the pseudo-complement of &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;b&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. This is the largest element &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;c&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; such that &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;≤&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;a&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;c \le a&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;c&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;∧&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi&gt;b&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;≤&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant=&#34;normal&#34;&gt;⊥&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;c \wedge b \le \bot&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
